#. [character_profile]: id=Galas, race=elf, gender=male
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:18
msgid "Galas"
msgstr ""

#. [character_profile]: id=Galas, race=elf, gender=male
#. [character_profile]: id=Anlindë, race=elf, gender=female
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:19 Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:50
msgid "Valley of Elynia"
msgstr ""

#. [character_profile]: id=Galas, race=elf, gender=male
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:24
msgid ""
"<b>Galas</b>, son of the late Captain Valthir, is a member of the southern "
"border patrol of the Valley of Elynia. Although born in the lush and cozy "
"forests of the inner Valley, from a very young age he took a liking to "
"accompanying his father in expeditions to safeguard the Valley from hostile "
"outsiders, learning the ins and outs of survival in the desert."
msgstr ""

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:28 Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:102
msgid "Alliance of the Peoples of the Far North"
msgstr ""

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:29
msgid ""
"As part of a barter to secure a new home for the forest elves in the Far "
"North, Galas pledged to join the Grand Council of the Northern Peoples, "
"along with Elynia and Mal Keshar. While doing so, he also renounced his "
"leadership of the elves, letting Lord Inodien take over his duties."
msgstr ""

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:35
msgid ""
"On the way back from Zocthanol Isle, Galas’s group was caught in a storm and "
"forced to make landfall in <b>Kalari Peninsula</b>, the location of the "
"<b>Iron Council</b> headquarters. Galas and Elynia were both captured by "
"Chaos forces during a struggle, resulting in a disastrous breakout attempt "
"where the two of them and Mal Keshar became lost in an underground "
"facility.\n"
"\n"
"While debating the best way to solve their predicament, the group was "
"ambushed by Elyssa, who emerged from the shadows and fatally struck Galas "
"from behind before anyone could react. Elynia and Mal Keshar narrowly "
"escaped via the use of teleport magic, but were ultimately unable to "
"retrieve the elf’s body."
msgstr ""

#. [character_profile]: id=Anlindë, race=elf, gender=female
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:49
msgid "Anlindë"
msgstr ""

#. [character_profile]: id=Anlindë, race=elf, gender=female
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:57
msgid ""
"While elves normally live for approximately three hundred years, <b>Anlindë</"
"b> is a rare exception whose presence in the Valley of Elynia is rumored to "
"predate the very existence of the settlement.\n"
"\n"
"Throughout the ages, Anlindë has dedicated herself to the tedious yet "
"crucial labor of record keeping for the valley’s governing council at "
"Telchior’s Keep, thus ensuring that old elven crafts and traditions—"
"especially those pertaining to the use of faerie magic—remain alive long "
"after the Great Fall. In more recent times however, her focus has largely "
"shifted away from desk jobs into tending to the sick and wounded, putting "
"her unrivaled mastery of herbal medicine into more practical uses.\n"
"\n"
"Since Captain Valthir’s unfortunate demise, Anlindë has taken care of his "
"only son <b>Galas</b> as if he were her own, even arranging for him to be "
"personally tutored by Lord Lédinor despite his father being a complete "
"outsider to the council."
msgstr ""

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:65
msgid ""
"During the elves’ first encounter with Mal Keshar, Anlindë’s magical prowess "
"proved far greater than suspected by anyone, as a single spell—of a nature "
"unknown to even the necromancer—allowed her to weaken him enough for Galas "
"and others to finish the job. Entirely unexpected to her, however, was Galas "
"and the lich’s mutual willingness to converse civilly; and even more "
"unexpected was how this would lead to an impromptu alliance without "
"precedent in elven history."
msgstr ""

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:70
msgid ""
"Upon meeting the <b>Lady of Light Elynia</b>, Galas, Mal Keshar, and Lady "
"Unarye learned the hidden truth behind Anlindë’s existence: she was once "
"part of the dark cult serving the <b>Demon Lord Zhangor</b> in Wesmere; "
"despite all the other priests having been executed to prevent a resurgence "
"of the wicked creature, Lord Telchior of Thelien chose to spare her life "
"alone for undisclosed reasons.\n"
"\n"
"In spite of this revelation, it was evident to all that Anlindë had "
"dedicated every instant of her continued existence to atoning for her sins "
"against elvenkind; not only that, but her advice to Lord Telchior became "
"directly responsible for the discovery of the valley which served as the "
"forest elves’ sanctuary for countless generations."
msgstr ""

#. [additional_info]
#. Keep "Chaos Warlord" gender-ambiguous if your language allows it
#. since this text will be visible in game before Elyssa's proper
#. reveal in S22A.
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:81
msgid ""
"In order to buy King Asthorgar and Galas time to evacuate Herthgar before "
"the Chaos Warlord’s final siege attempt, Anlindë chose to stay behind and "
"defend the capital with the assistance of Mal Keshar’s minions and a few "
"dwarven troops. Everybody knew that it would be extremely unlikely for her "
"to survive the encounter, and indeed, she never returned from her mission. "
"Her sacrifice was not in vain, however, as it allowed the evacuation to "
"proceed mostly as planned with minimal loss of life."
msgstr ""

#. [character_profile]: id=Mal Keshar, race=undead, gender=male
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:88
msgid "Mal Keshar"
msgstr ""

#. [character_profile]: id=Mal Keshar, race=undead, gender=male
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:96
msgid ""
"<b>Mal Keshar</b> — formerly <b>Malin Keshar</b> — is an ancient Lich from "
"the times before the Fall, hailing from the old human kingdom known as "
"<b>Wesnoth</b>.\n"
"\n"
"His origins can be traced back to the border town of Parthyn, at the time "
"afflicted by constant orcish incursions. The timely intervention of a "
"necromancer known as <b>Darken Volk</b> during a battle which cost Parthyn "
"many lives, including that of Malin Keshar’s father, prompted the young boy "
"to begin his travels and apprenticeship under the dark mage. While his "
"master’s fate has been lost to history, what is known is that Malin Keshar "
"attained lichdom and became the bane of the orcish tribes for a thousand "
"years."
msgstr ""

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:103
msgid ""
"As part of Galas’s barter to secure a new home for the forest elves in the "
"Far North, Mal Keshar pledged allegiance to the <b>Grand Council of the "
"Northern Peoples</b>."
msgstr ""

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:108
msgid ""
"Mal Keshar proved a decisive factor in overcoming the obstacles Galas’s "
"group encountered on their way to the lair of the <b>Chaos Emperor</b> in "
"Inferno. Unfortunately, the severe amount of damage he sustained from "
"fighting Elyssa, Argan, and Elynia in quick succession caused his power to "
"wane considerably. Despite this, Mal Keshar continued to be a force to be "
"reckoned with, rivaling even the most powerful priests and necromancers at "
"Uria’s service."
msgstr ""

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:115
msgid ""
"At the end of the group’s confrontation with the empowered <b>Shaxthal "
"Queen</b> at the Wesmere Hive’s Abaddon facility, Mal Keshar and all his "
"undead minions were caught in the massive whirlpool of energy released from "
"the beast’s shattered core, causing his soul to be forcibly released from "
"his body. Only minutes after, the entire facility along with the ruined "
"plains of Wesmere completely vanished off the face of Irdya."
msgstr ""

#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:121
msgid ""
"Following their participation in the War of Wesmere, Elynia and Argan "
"descended into the deepest reaches the Heart Mountains seeking answers "
"regarding the Demon Lord and his place of origin. Tragically, an earthquake "
"caused the earth to claim Argan’s life, not even leaving a body for Elynia "
"to retrieve. Stricken with grief, the faerie requested the assistance of "
"dwarves to seal her in a custom-built burial chamber, intending to lay "
"dormant until the day Irdya would recover from complete devastation."
msgstr ""

#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:125
msgid ""
"Galas’s band confronted Argan in his own lair in the frozen wastes of "
"Inferno, initially finding themselves completely outclassed by the sorcerer. "
"However, Elynia’s ingenuity allowed her to fight him on equal ground by "
"channeling the Power of the Union straight from him at close quarters. "
"Despite <b>Uria</b> attempting to turn the tide by mutating and puppeteering "
"Argan’s body, Elynia managed to subdue him with Galas and Mal Keshar’s help. "
"Unable to find an alternative solution to her quandary, she struck at his "
"heart with the full extent of her own power, thus putting an end to his "
"sinister reign over Irdya."
msgstr ""

#. [character_profile]: id=Elynia, race=faerie, gender=female
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:130
msgid "Elynia, the Lady of Light"
msgstr ""

#. [character_profile]: id=Elynia, race=faerie, gender=female
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:136
msgid "Source of Light, Protector of the Elves of Irdya"
msgstr ""

#. [character_profile]: id=Elynia, race=faerie, gender=female
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:137
msgid "Ka’lian of Wesmere (before the Fall)"
msgstr ""

#. [character_profile]: id=Elynia, race=faerie, gender=female
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:147
msgid ""
"Better known by elves and humans as the <b>Lady of Light</b> throughout "
"history before the Fall, <b>Elynia</b> is one of the two heroes that once "
"wielded the Union of Light and Darkness against Irdya’s greatest foe, the "
"<b>Demon Lord Zhangor</b>.\n"
"\n"
"Although very few records remain of her past life amongst elvenkind, it is "
"believed that she was raised in the great woods of Wesmere by an enchantress "
"who had close ties with the old Ka’lian. Having attained a seemingly eternal "
"lifespan through her mastery of Light, Elynia once made a name for herself "
"by achieving many feats as a wandering peace-keeper traveling all across the "
"Great Continent. Although the civilizations of the Golden Era are long gone, "
"a few hazy legends resulting from her participation in past events still "
"linger in the public consciousness."
msgstr ""

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:155
msgid ""
"Alliance of the Peoples of the Far North, Ka’lian of Wesmere (before the "
"Fall)"
msgstr ""

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:156
msgid ""
"As part of Galas’s barter to secure a new home for the forest elves in the "
"Far North, Elynia pledged allegiance to the <b>Grand Council of the Northern "
"Peoples</b>."
msgstr ""

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:161
msgid ""
"Owing to twisted machinations of fate, Elynia’s partner <b>Argan</b>—once "
"known as the <b>Master of Darkness</b> and co-wielder of the Union of Light "
"and Darkness—became Uria’s most valued vassal and took upon the title of "
"<b>Chaos Emperor</b>."
msgstr ""

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:169
msgid "Source of Light, Protector of the Elves of Irdya, Eloh"
msgstr ""

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:176
msgid ""
"Alliance of the Peoples of the Far North (formerly), Ka’lian of Wesmere "
"(before the Fall)"
msgstr ""

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:181
msgid ""
"Sent by the <b>Demon Lord Ergea</b> in search of a “power hidden beneath "
"Kalari”, Elynia confronted the <b>Chaos Warlord Elyssa</b> in an abandoned "
"underground section of the stronghold. This time, the demoness made no "
"secret of her possession of Yechnagoth’s legacy as the <b>Guardian of "
"Darkness</b>, and promptly killed Elynia in combat."
msgstr ""

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:186
msgid "Elynia, the Guardian of Earth"
msgstr ""

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:187
msgid "Lady of Light, Source of Light, Protector of the Elves of Irdya, Eloh"
msgstr ""

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:188
#, fuzzy
msgid "The Ten Guardians"
msgstr "Guardiano infernale"

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:189
msgid ""
"Some time after, Elynia came back to life as the <b>Guardian of Earth</b> on "
"Irdya. Despite her godlike potential, she has been unable to make proper use "
"of her power due to a complete lack of understanding of her situation—her "
"<i>curse</i>—coupled with an intense pain beyond description."
msgstr ""

#. [character_profile]: id=Elyssa, race=shaxthal, gender=female
#. Keep "Chaos Warlord" gender-ambiguous if your language allows it.
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:197
#, fuzzy
msgid "female^Chaos Warlord"
msgstr "corazzata"

#. [character_profile]: id=Elyssa, race=shaxthal, gender=female
#. [character_profile]: id=Uria, race=demon, gender=female
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:203 Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:291
#, fuzzy
msgid "Chaos Empire"
msgstr "Razziatore del Caos"

#. [character_profile]: id=Elyssa, race=shaxthal, gender=female
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:214
msgid ""
"Evidence suggests that this seemingly half-machine, half-human creature "
"serves as the Chaos Emperor’s right hand, enforcing his will and instilling "
"fear and respect into his enemies and servants alike even in his absence."
msgstr ""

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:218
msgid "Elyssa, the Chaos Warlord"
msgstr ""

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:219
#, fuzzy
msgid "Fire of Uria"
msgstr "Spirito di Fuoco"

#. [additional_info]
#. [additional_info]: race=shaxthal
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:220 Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:267
msgid "Chaos Empire’s Iron Council"
msgstr ""

#. [additional_info]
#. Keep "Chaos Warlord" gender-ambiguous if your language allows it.
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:227
msgid ""
"Following her defeat at the hands of the Lady of Light and Mal Keshar, the "
"Chaos Warlord revealed herself to be <b>Elyssa</b>, a former scholar who "
"dedicated her life to studying the ancient Wesnoth Empire’s history. "
"Additional information from the dwarves of Herthgar indicates that a Red "
"Mage matching her description once journeyed alongside Kalehssar’s people "
"and spent time with the dwarves of Gnalvarden before disappearing back into "
"the sands. It is currently unknown what events resulted in her "
"transformation into the monstrous biomechanical demon she is now.\n"
"\n"
"Following Anlindë's self-sacrifice in the capital of Herthgar, Elyssa "
"confronted the heroes in the lower levels of the Heart and nearly won, were "
"it not for Elynia’s use Light magic to temporarily blind her in order to "
"escape and regroup. Although Elyssa eventually found the band again, by then "
"Elynia and Mal Keshar had figured out how to channel the Darkness magic "
"radiating from the Chaos fortress in order to empower themselves with the "
"Union of Light and Darkness. After forcing Elyssa to retreat and regroup "
"multiple times, the duo managed to defeat the demoness in direct combat, but "
"Elynia chose at the last moment to spare her life rather than execute her."
msgstr ""

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:235
msgid "Guardian of Darkness, Fire of Uria"
msgstr ""

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:240
msgid "Elyssa, the Guardian of Darkness"
msgstr ""

#. [additional_info]
#. Keep "Chaos Warlord" gender-ambiguous if your language allows it.
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:242
msgid "Chaos Warlord, Fire of Uria"
msgstr ""

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:243
msgid "Chaos Empire’s Iron Council (formerly)"
msgstr ""

#. [character_profile]: id=Argan, race=human, gender=male
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:250
msgid "Argan, the Master of Darkness"
msgstr ""

#. [character_profile]: id=Argan, race=human, gender=male
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:257
msgid ""
"Better known by elves and humans as the <b>Master of Darkness</b> throughout "
"history before the Fall, <b>Argan</b> is one of the two heroes that once "
"wielded the Union of Light and Darkness against Irdya’s greatest foe, the "
"<b>Demon Lord Zhangor</b>.\n"
"\n"
"Very few records exist of Argan’s past life, and absolutely none of his "
"story before first encountering <b>Elynia</b>, the one who would eventually "
"become his lover and co-wielder of the Union. Past elven scholars would even "
"dare suggest that he was not really from the Great Continent, owing to his "
"sudden appearance and lack of knowledge about the world at the time."
msgstr ""

#. [additional_info]: race=shaxthal
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:265
msgid "Argan, the Chaos Emperor"
msgstr ""

#. [additional_info]: race=shaxthal
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:266
msgid "Master of Darkness, Voice of Uria, Mal-Zagarn"
msgstr ""

#. [additional_info]: race=shaxthal
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:276
msgid ""
"Owing to twisted machinations of fate, Argan became Uria’s most valued "
"vassal and took upon the title of <b>Chaos Emperor</b> in this era on "
"Irdya.\n"
"\n"
"Following his accident in the Heart Mountains, Argan was somehow found by "
"Uria and reshaped into a humanoid biomechanical creature wielding a fragment "
"of her power, becoming her anointed Voice on Irdya. Aided by the power of "
"demons from Inferno, he united the peoples of the Great Desert and various "
"coastal regions into one Chaos Empire, with the ultimate aim of subduing and "
"encompassing all of Irdya."
msgstr ""

#. [character_profile]: id=Uria, race=demon, gender=female
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:286
msgid "Uria"
msgstr ""

#. [character_profile]: id=Uria, race=demon, gender=female
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:290
msgid "Mother of All Demons"
msgstr ""

#. [character_profile]: id=Uria, race=demon, gender=female
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:294
msgid ""
"The soldiers and demons at the Chaos Empire’s service mention <b>Uria</b> "
"very often, referring to her as an unforgiving yet highly-respected goddess. "
"Past records do seldom mention one such Uria, claimed to be the <b>Mother of "
"All Demons</b>, the creator of all monsters who were once relegated to "
"<b>Inferno</b>."
msgstr ""

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:298
msgid "Uria, the Guardian of Life"
msgstr ""

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:299
msgid "Mother of All Demons, Goddess of Life, Mistress of the Void"
msgstr ""

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:300
msgid "The Ten Guardians, Chaos Empire"
msgstr ""

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:301
msgid ""
"It turns out that Uria is not only real, but also unlike Yechnagoth she is "
"very much alive and active within her domain. She is occasionally identified "
"as the <b>Guardian of Life</b>, one of ten powerful demons of old with "
"godlike powers over the different aspects of the universe.\n"
"\n"
"The late <b>Chaos Emperor Argan</b> served as her <b>Voice</b>, her emissary "
"and highest authority on Irdya; the one in charge of communicating her will "
"to the <b>Iron Triad</b> and the Lorekeepers of the Empire.\n"
"\n"
"Upon realizing that Argan might not win the fight against Galas’s group on "
"his own, Uria attempted to turn the tide by mutating and puppeteering his "
"body."
msgstr ""

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/profiles.cfg:310
msgid ""
"She subsequently attempted the same tactic by turning <b>Lédinor</b> into a "
"thrall during the group’s escape from the collapsing capital."
msgstr ""

#. [story_recap]: id=UtBS
#: Naia/journey/recap.cfg:5
msgid "Under the Burning Suns"
msgstr ""

#. [story_recap]: id=UtBS
#: Naia/journey/recap.cfg:6
msgid ""
"One fateful night, the young <b>Kalehssar</b> of the <b>Quenoth elves</b> "
"hears the voice of the goddess <b>Eloh</b> in his sleep, warning him of a "
"great disaster that will require him to lead his people out of the desert "
"under her guidance. He is then abruptly woken up by utter pandemonium as "
"rocks rain from the sky, laying waste to the elves’ home in the desert and "
"ending many lives.\n"
"\n"
"With Kaleh turning out to be the closest surviving relative of their late "
"leader Tanuil, and necromancers and other barbarians threatening to take "
"advantage of the chaos and finish them off, the desert elves rally under his "
"command and accept his instruction to lead an exodus across the sands in "
"search of a new home.\n"
"\n"
"After a long and treacherous journey through the desert, the Quenoth elves "
"arrive at a mountain range. Kaleh has once again been visited by their "
"goddess in his dreams and been advised to lead his people underground to get "
"past the mountains. Despite some initial reluctance, the elves descend into "
"the depths, braving many obstacles along the way but also making new "
"steadfast allies in the darkness.\n"
"\n"
"As he and his people finally reach the surface, Kaleh is visited by the "
"goddess again; this time she manifests not in his dreams, but while he is "
"wide awake in the physical realm. The encounter quickly turns sour once Eloh "
"notices that the elf has not only opted not to exterminate the denizens of "
"the underground like she planned, but even gone as far as to befriend them. "
"The leader of a troop of humans arrives and suspects the Quenoth elves of "
"slaughtering his kinsmen despite them arriving to the surface after the "
"fact. When the human announces his decision to bring the elves to the "
"<b>Iron Council</b> for judgment, Eloh commands Kaleh to submit to their "
"will; sensing something amiss, Kaleh refuses, earning him the scorn of Eloh "
"and the humans both, and igniting an armed confrontation with the latter as "
"the goddess vanishes.\n"
"\n"
"Some time after the elves have successfully repelled the human soldiers, a "
"scouting party returns with a bizarre aquatic creature communicating his "
"leader’s desire to speak in person with Kaleh. Soon, the elves learn that "
"the creature is a merman, and an emissary of the high priestess of his "
"people. As the merfok appear to know crucial information about Kaleh’s "
"predicament, he agrees to help the merman rescue his brethren, who are being "
"held captive for ritual sacrifice by the humans.\n"
"\n"
"Soon, the elves successfully infiltrate the Iron Council’s coastal "
"settlement in Ygriz, managing to rescue some of the merfolk so that they can "
"guide them to their high priestess. Before they can do so, however, Eloh "
"makes a new appearance, this time visible to everyone; she reveals Kaleh’s "
"disobedience and betrayal to all, and successfully turns many of his "
"compatriots against him. In order to quell the ensuing dispute and avoid "
"further bloodshed, Kaleh sneaks past the rebels’ forces and destroys the "
"physical avatar of Eloh, declaring her a mere impostor intent on sowing "
"discord amongst the elves to accelerate their destruction.\n"
"\n"
"Kaleh’s people commandeer some of the ships at the Iron Council’s "
"headquarters and sail off the Great Continent into the open ocean, where "
"they finally meet the high priestess <b>Melusand</b> of the merfolk. The "
"mermaid reveals the truth behind the impostor: she turns out to be a dark "
"goddess able to corrupt and control the minds of creatures, with faerie "
"beings such as elves and merfolk being the most naturally resistant to her "
"influence; her name is <b>Yechnagoth, the Eater of Souls</b>.\n"
"\n"
"Well aware that the goddess already has set her sights on them and "
"confrontation is inevitable no matter where they go next, Kaleh and his "
"friends decide to lead an all-out assault on Yechnagoth’s residence in "
"<b>Zocthanol Isle</b> with the merfolk’s assistance. Once they take most of "
"her defensive forces down, the false Eloh makes a new appearance and invites "
"Kaleh to join her for a personal audience at her citadel. Despite his "
"friends’ protests, he acquiesces and heads into Eloh’s sanctum alone; this "
"does not stop them from secretly following him, however.\n"
"\n"
"Inside Yechnagoth’s lair, Kaleh’s friends find him seemingly unconscious on "
"the ground, while the goddess shows them how she is able to brainwash even "
"elves now that they are all gathered in her own dominion. Kaleh stands up "
"and seemingly obeys Yechnagoth’s command, only to stab her in an act of "
"defiance the moment he is close enough to her. After a brief confrontation "
"with the brainwashed elves, the enraged goddess reveals her true form, that "
"of a colossal, twisted, dark abomination with no discernible body features "
"other than veins brimming with teal blood. Despite facing a creature unlike "
"anything they had ever seen before, Kaleh and his group prevail against her "
"and her progeny, destroying her and releasing her armies from her control; "
"thus the Eater of Souls’ brief reign on Irdya comes to an end.\n"
"\n"
"The Quenoth elves proceed to clean up the now-abandoned island, renaming it "
"<b>Quenoth Isle</b>, and adopting it as their new permanent home."
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=Irdya
#: Naia/journey/world.cfg:5
msgid "Irdya"
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=Irdya
#: Naia/journey/world.cfg:6
msgid ""
"<b>Irdya</b> is the name of this vast world. It has existed since time "
"immemorial and gone through countless changes, the latest of which is a "
"devastating event known as <b>the Great Fall</b>, or more simply, <b>the "
"Fall</b>.\n"
"\n"
"Populated by many varied creatures—both sapient and otherwise—Irdya was once "
"a thriving realm that saw the rise and fall of many civilizations, most of "
"them learned in at least one form of magic or technology: humans, elves, "
"dwarves, orcs, to name a few.\n"
"\n"
"Irdya has two suns, named <b>Sela</b> and <b>Naia</b>, as well as one moon "
"occasionally known as <b>Eidyia</b>. Some ancient records of dubious origin "
"claim that a second, smaller moon could seldom be spotted in the times when "
"only Sela roamed the skies.\n"
"\n"
"The largest landmass on Irdya is known as the <b>Great Continent</b>. Much "
"of its geography changed drastically after the Fall, and the current state "
"of civilization has made it impossible to properly chart the alterations."
msgstr ""

#. [additional_info]
#: Naia/journey/world.cfg:17
msgid ""
"Irdya is one of ten worlds where a primordial construct known as a <b>Seed</"
"b> was planted; Irdya’s is the <b>Seed of Earth</b>, which during the First "
"Cycle gave way to the dominion of <b>Xia’el</b>, Guardian of Earth."
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=The_Fall
#: Naia/journey/world.cfg:24
msgid "The Fall"
msgstr ""

#. [world_entry]: id=The_Fall
#: Naia/journey/world.cfg:25
msgid ""
"A long time ago, the world of <b>Irdya</b> was completely transformed by a "
"cataclysm referred to as <b>the Great Fall</b>, or more simply, <b>the Fall</"
"b>.\n"
"\n"
"Much of what is currently “known” about the calamity that befell Irdya has "
"been pieced together from fragments passed down through oral tradition by "
"the peoples who survived the turmoil.\n"
"\n"
"It is said that at the exact time of the catastrophe, a deafening boom "
"louder than even the greatest volcanic eruption was heard; the next instant, "
"the earth violently shook and tore asunder, crumbling every bastion of the "
"old empires to dust and sinking even some of the tallest mountains to the "
"depths of the world. Volcanoes everywhere stirred to life and poured molten "
"rock and poisonous ash into the now darkened skies; then, the Vast Ocean "
"rose to meet the clouds before fiercely descending upon the land, claiming "
"what little remained standing after the initial convulsion.\n"
"\n"
"Untold millions perished at the hands of Irdya herself; then in the "
"aftermath, millions more were massacred by the panic-stricken in their "
"senseless frenzy. The impenetrable veil in the sky not only denied all of "
"navigational aid, but also caused all plant life to wither away even in "
"places that had not been directly touched by destruction yet; whether it be "
"from the poisonous rain, or from the accursed darkness that suffocated the "
"earth and submerged all into a timeless haze. Soon, any leaders left or "
"risen amongst the ashes of civilization would resort to barbarism and unholy "
"practices in a desperate attempt to perpetuate their pitiable existences in "
"the warped new world.\n"
"\n"
"Thus, the <b>Golden Age</b> of the peoples of Irdya came to its end.\n"
"\n"
"Many years later, the suns <b>Sela</b> and <b>Naia</b> would finally return, "
"only to turn the once verdant Great Continent into a barren husk of rock and "
"sand; a place where all kinds of life battle each other for survival at day, "
"and vengeful spectres of the past haunt the dunes at night."
msgstr ""

